title: "Zairn: Open-Source Location Sharing & Geo-Anchored Content Platform"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Zairn Contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/zairn-dev/Zairn"
url: "https://github.com/zairn-dev/Zairn"
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-03-12"
keywords:
  - location-sharing
  - geofencing
  - zero-knowledge-proof
  - ipfs
  - supabase
  - geodrop
  - privacy
  - open-source
abstract: >-
  An open-source location-sharing platform combining Zenly-style
  real-time friend location sharing with Sekai Camera-style
  geo-anchored content (GeoDrop). Features include pluggable
  location verification (GPS, secret, AR, ZKP), client-side
  AES-256-GCM encryption with location-derived keys, IPFS/on-chain
  persistence, and zero-knowledge proof of proximity using
  Groth16/snarkjs.
